HEADWORD: Reseminate
<hw>Re*sem"i*nate</hw> <pr>(-s?m"?-n?t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
pref. <ets>re-</ets> again + <ets>seminatus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>seminare</ets> to sow.]</ety> <def>To produce again by means of
seed.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir. T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

